Im sorry but I don't understand why it is an issue that fighters are fit. Asking for a female akin to the female barbarian in d3 is unrealistic because it is biologically difficult for women to achieve that physique. It is more unrealistic to be asking for that sort of thing than to have all the women in the game have the typical physique of a fit woman. 

I understand some are over-sexualized but if a girl is sexy and is aware of it, they tend to flaunt it. There are plenty of unsexualized females. 

There is a line that is being blurred between having an hourglass figure, which happens to being biologically natural for women with little to no fat, and being sexualized. An example is kayle, Kayle is a warrior, she isnt going to have a ton of fat on her. So yea, naturally her figure is going to rely on her bone structure, which happens to look like an hourglass in women. Have you even researched why women tend to have an hourglass figure? It is natural. Quit bitching just because you want what you dont have.

You don't see us skinny men complaining about all the warrior's having 6 packs and being unrealistically beefy, I'm lookin' at you {{champion:86}}
